

I want you to generate a complete Vue + Laravel/MySQL feature called `myproject_tasks`. Follow these requirements exactly:  1. **Backend (Laravel 12, API routes)**:    - Create a `MyProjectTask` model and migration with fields:       - `id` (auto-increment)      - `title` (string)      - `description` (text)      - `status` (enum: 'pending', 'in_progress', 'completed')      - `priority` (enum: 'low', 'medium', 'high')      - `due_date` (date)      - `created_at`, `updated_at`    - Create a `MyProjectTaskController` with full REST API:      - `index` → list all tasks with optional filters: `status`, `priority`, `search by title/description`      - `store` → create new task      - `show` → show single task      - `update` → update task      - `destroy` → delete task    - Make API routes for these in `api.php`, grouped under `/api/myproject_tasks`.  2. **Frontend (Vue 3 with `<script setup>` and Axios)**:    - Place all frontend files in `developer/myproject_tasks` folder.    - Create pages/components for:      - **Task List**: displays all tasks in a table with columns: Title, Status, Priority, Due Date, Actions.        - Include filters at the top: Status (dropdown), Priority (dropdown), Search (input)        - Actions: Edit, Delete      - **Task Form**: for creating/editing tasks        - Fields: Title, Description, Status, Priority, Due Date        - Validate fields before submit    - Use Axios `.then()` syntax for all API calls.    - Show real-time success/error notifications.    - Use clean, modern UI styling (Tailwind or Bootstrap classes).  3. **Additional Requirements**:    - Ensure the frontend works fully with the backend API.    - Include proper error handling for network/API errors.    - Include code comments explaining each part.    - Make the filter at the top functional: changing any filter automatically updates the table.  4. **Bonus**:    - Make the table sortable by columns.    - Paginate results if tasks exceed 10 per page.  Generate **all necessary backend and frontend code** including migrations, models, controllers, API routes, Vue components/pages, and Axios calls. 

